5:
*sigh* Nothing, nothing, and more
nothing as far as the eye can see.
9:
We've been trekking since morning,
and I'm starting to get hungry...
*sniff* Huh?
14:
What that smell? Is someone having
a barbecue?
20:
No... This is the stench of burnt land
and wood. Come, we must hurry!
26:
Stella, wait! Don't stray too far from
us!
31: Mister... Mister! Are you all right?
40:
Please... I have a favor to ask of you...
There's a farm... where all the other
survivors have gone... Take the
children there...
41:
I know we're perfect strangers... But
I've no one else to rely on... Please... I
beg of you...
44:
Don't worry. I'll make sure they reach
safety.
53: He's still breathing, but it's faint...
55:
...Sorry. I should've consulted with
the group before making any
promises. I'll understand if you don't
want to come with me.
63:
We are ALL going. Nimbus, can you
carry that man?
75:
Don't be afraid. I won't let anything
happen to you.
79:
This the farm? Looks more like a
fortress.
82: Around here, it's not easy to survive.
83: Looks like they don't trust us...
88: Let us in. We have children with us.
93:
They were with an old man next to a
burning carriage. Does that sound
familiar?
96:
I... I can't believe it!
Wait just a moment! I'm opening up
the gates!
101:
Thank the stars you darlings are
safe... You must've been so scared...
Mommy's sorry... Mommy's sorry she
couldn't go back for you!
103:
On behalf of everyone living in this
village, I wanted to say thank you.
We owe you everything.
105:
You owe us nothing. We were only
keeping a promise.
107:
I just wish we'd made it in time to
save your father...
110:
I'm grateful he was able to pass
among his own people. I'm sure he
feels the same.
111:
Now, it's starting to get dark. Why
don't you put up your weary feet
and stay here for the night?
121:
I'm glad we could reunite the kids
with their families.
125:
Why do you think their carriage was
the only one attacked?
129:
Apparently, it was the last in the
caravan. They were hit by
washed-up adventurers. It's just like
those cowards to go after stragglers.
132:
Come to think of it, we've dealt with
"washed-up adventurers" before.
When we first met Mormia.
136:
We're a long way from Palpebra.
There's no Kaleidoscope here, which
means barely any money and
barely any people.
137:
It's the perfect place for a group of
armed failures to run wild.
139:
When that carriage was attacked,
I'm sure the rest of the caravan
wanted to help—but with what
firepower? Turning back would've
just invited more tragedy.
143: ...Is there no hope for this village?
147:
Since I was young, I've seen plenty of
places like this. And all of them have
fallen.
155:
You really think a few sticks was
gonna keep us out? I'd have more
trouble raidin' an anthill!
157:
I wouldn't run if I were you... Fun's
about to start now.
162:
Were you the ones who attacked
that carriage?
165:
Carriage?
...Oh, she means that little
wagon—the one that didn't have no
valuables in it! Hell, it wasn't even
worth remembering!
167:
What? You here for revenge? I'm
always ready to dance with a pretty—
171:
Funny you should ask that. Thanks
to you, it feels like I've found myself
again.
172:
I finally understand why I spent all
those years training... and why I
came back to this place.
175:
What's someone like you doing on
this run-down farm?
176:
With skills like yours, you could be
guardin' manors for five—no, ten
times the pay!
179:
Maybe. But I'm not in it for the
money.
181: Then why the hell are you...
183:
I fight to defend people who have
no one else.
186:
Looks like we owe you everything
and more now! I won't ever forget
what you did for us!
189: I did what I felt was right. That's all.
193:
...Let me give you some advice.
You're living in lawless territory.
You'd better get out as soon as you
can.
197:
And even then, if you ever find
yourself in trouble, know you can
rely on my sword.
199:
Doesn't matter when. I'll come
running.
206:
Hey, Mormia. You still planning on
traveling with us?
211:
You've found purpose, right? I'm
guessing you don't really care about
going home anymore.
215:
You guessed right. But your
adventures take you to far-flung
places—and that's where my sword
is needed most.
217:
...Are you trying to hint you don't
want me around?
224:
Good. Because I'm here to stay. Just
like you.
